{"name": "pyramid-beaker", "metadata": {"name": "pyramid_beaker", "version": "0.9", "classifiers": ["Framework :: Pyramid", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy"], "home_page": "https://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid_beaker/en/latest/", "license": "BSD-derived (http://www.repoze.org/LICENSE.txt)", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pyramid", "beaker"], "summary": "Beaker session factory backend for Pyramid", "upload_time": 1712298764}, "documentation": ["# pyramid_beaker\n\nProvides a session factory for the [Pyramid](https://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/pyramid/en/latest/)\nweb framework backed by the [Beaker](https://beaker.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) sessioning\nsystem.\n\n## 0.9 (2024-03-29)\n\n> - Fixed a bug causing session saving even when it is not needed. See\n>   <https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_beaker/pull/28>\n\n## 0.8 (2013-06-28)\n\n- On Python 3, the CSRF token returned by new_csrf_token was a bytestring\n  instead of correctly being a string.  See\n  <https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_beaker/pull/12>\n- A new argument to PyramidBeakerSessionFactoryConfig named\n  `constant_csrf_token` is now permitted for test configuration purposes.\n  See <https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_beaker/pull/13> for more information.\n\n## 0.7 (2012-07-10)\n\n- Python 3.2 compatibility.\n- Dropped Jython support (may be re-added after Jython releases a 2.7-\n  compatible version).\n- Dropped Python 2.5 support.\n- Made compatible with zope.interface 4.0.0 (symptom: `TypeError: Class\n  advice impossible in Python3.  Use the @implementer class decorator\n  instead.` when run under Python 2 or *or* Python 3)\n- Add `dev` and `docs` setup.py aliases.\n\n## 0.6.1 (2011-11-19)\n\n- Beaker 1.6+ compat: added support for `key_length` and `enabled`\n  options.\n\n## 0.6 (2011-11-12)\n\n- Add a tox.ini for Jenkins testing.\n- Add includeme function to ease application setup.\n\n## 0.5 (2011-03-30)\n\n- The default value for the `cookie_on_exception` parameter to\n  `pyramid_beaker.BeakerSessionFactoryConfig` is now `True`.  This means\n  that when view code causes an exception to be raised, and the session has\n  been mutated, a cookie will be sent back in the response.  Previously its\n  default value was `False`.\n\n## 0.4 (2011-01-08)\n\n- Allow cache regions to inherit URL configuration from main cache options.\n- Respect a `cookie_on_exception` configuration value passed to the\n  `BeakerSessionFactoryConfig` constructor.  If this value is passed and\n  it's not false, session cookies will be set even on responses resulting\n  from an exception.\n- Update to new relationship between `new_csrf_token` and\n  `get_csrf_token` as described in Pyramid 1.0a9 interfaces.\n\n## 0.3 (2010-12-29)\n\n- Support ISession flash/csrf API added to Pyramid 1.0a8+.\n\n## 0.2 (2010-11-27)\n\n- Add cache_region support via\n  `pyramid_beaker.set_cache_regions_from_settings` (and documented).\n\n## 0.1\n\n- Initial release.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pyramid_beaker", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pyramid_beaker.BeakerSessionFactoryConfig", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "**options", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a Pyramid session factory using Beaker session settings\nsupplied directly as ``**options``"]}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.call_save", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "wrapped", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["By default, in non-auto-mode beaker badly wants people to\ncall save even though it should know something has changed when\na mutating method is called.  This hack should be removed if\nBeaker ever starts to do this by default. "]}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.session_factory_from_settings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "settings", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a Pyramid session factory using Beaker session settings\nsupplied from a Paste configuration file"]}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.set_cache_regions_from_settings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "settings", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add cache support to the Pylons application.\n\nThe `settings` passed to the configurator are used to setup\nthe cache options. Cache options in the settings should start\nwith either 'beaker.cache.' or 'cache.'.\n"]}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.includeme", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pyramid_beaker.asbool", "xref": {"fqname": "pyramid.settings.asbool", "project": "pyramid"}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.cache", "xref": {"fqname": "beaker.cache", "project": "beaker"}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.coerce_cache_params", "xref": {"fqname": "beaker.util.coerce_cache_params", "project": "beaker"}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.coerce_session_params", "xref": {"fqname": "beaker.util.coerce_session_params", "project": "beaker"}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.hexlify", "xref": {"fqname": "binascii.hexlify", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.implementer", "xref": {"fqname": "zope.interface.implementer", "project": null}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.ISession", "xref": {"fqname": "pyramid.interfaces.ISession", "project": "pyramid"}}, {"name": "pyramid_beaker.SessionObject", "xref": {"fqname": "beaker.session.SessionObject", "projec